<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gebreselassie Auctions Sports Wear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Olympic 10,000
meters champion Haile Gebreselassie has auctioned one of his
sports wear for 50,000 birr (about 6,200 U.S. dollars) to support
a sports club in Addis Ababa, the Ethiopian Herald newspapers
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Buyers offered between 25,000-40,000 birr (nearly 5,000 U.S.
dollars) for Gebreselassie's sports wear, which he put on at the
Atlanta Olympics when he triumphed in the 10,000 meters.
</P>
<P>
But the track superstar beat these offers by giving out 50,000
birr, the report said.
</P>
<P>
There were also four pieces of sports wear for auction. These
were offered by Abebe Mekone, Belayneh Densamo, Fita Bayisa and
Gete Wami.
</P>
<P>
Like Gebreselassie, both Mekone and Densamo gave the best price
for their sports wear offered to the auction meeting, and remained
to be the owners of their own outfits.
</P>
<P>
A total sum of 206,000 birr (about 25,000 U.S. dollars) was
obtained from the sale of sports wear and donations, the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
