<HEADLINE> Kuwait Grants Loan to Zambia on Road Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will construct a
70-kilometre tarred road in its Western Province with foreign
loans including 10 million U.S. dollars granted by Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Hesham Ebraheem Al-Waqayan, deputy director of the Kuwait Fund
for Arab Economic Development, said at the signing ceremony on
Thursday that the 20- year loan provided by the Kuwaiti government
would cover about 29 percent of the total cost of the project,
which will be completed by the year 2003.
</P>
<P>
Al-Waqayan said Kuwait is willing to work with the Zambian
government to initiate other projects in the country.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Finance and Economic Minister Katele Kalumba said the
total cost of the project is 27.3 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said co-operating partners BADEA (Arab Bank for Economic
Development of Africa in Khatoum) and Vienna-based OPEC will put
in 10.7 million and four million U.S. dollars respectively and the
government of Zambia will provide the remaining 2.6 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Kalumba said the opening of the road would provide Zambia with
a shorter route to the port of Lobito in Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
