<HEADLINE> Japan to Increase Assistance to Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 6 (Xinhua) -- Zambia and Japan signed an
agreement here Thursday to increase Japanese assistance to Zambia
in the fields of poverty reduction, health, education and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Finance Minister Katele Kalumba said at the signing
ceremony his country attached great importance to the
consultations with Japan, because it is only through dialogue that
the two countries can develop a common understanding and vision on
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He urged Japan to invest in his country's electricity and
telecommunications sectors.
</P>
<P>
Kalumba said it is now the time for the two countries to create
the necessary conditions for the private sectors in both countries
to interact and exploit the available business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Shinsuke Horiuchi, head of the visiting Japanese delegation,
said the two governments are engaged in an intensive dialogue on
strategies for poverty reduction in Zambia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
