<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Imports Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan imports reached 12.67
billion U.S. dollars last year, dropping by 11 percent compared
with 1998, due to the recession in the country, said the
Statistics and Informatics Central Office (OCEI) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The United States was the first exporter to Venezuela in 1999,
with 5.19 billion dollars, followed by Colombia with 737 million
dollars, Italy with 734 million, Germany with 613 million, and
Mexico with 489 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela imported 4.38 billion dollars of electricity
materials, as well as chemicals, with 1.43 billion dollars, and
transportation materials, with 1.28 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
