<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Non-Aligned Movement Countries Hold Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARTAGENA, Colombia, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The 13th Non-Aligned
Movement Countries (NALM) Ministerial Conference's preparatory
meeting was opened Friday in Cartagena, north of Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Colombian Ambassador to the United Nations Alfonso Valdivieso
presided over the inaugural ceremony, that was attended by high-
ranking officials from 95 of the 115 NALM member countries.
</P>
<P>
Valdivieso expressed his concern about recent cases in which
the efforts of several years to consolidate peace have failed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the processes of political negotiation for a peace
agreement and for its consolidation must be respected and duly
supported by the international community.
</P>
<P>
He said that the outlook for a nuclear disarmament is not very
clear, and that for this reason the Non-Aligned Movement must be
very emphatic about the imperative need to clear of obstructions
the disarmament agenda.
</P>
<P>
The NALM 13th Conference will be held on April 8-9 to examine
the progress and implementation of the Movement Summit, held in
Durban, South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
