<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Analysis: Blix Seeks to Make UNMOVIC Different From UNSCOM By Xie Meihua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Hans Blix, Executive
Chairman of the United Nations Monitoring, Verification and
Inspection Commission(UNMOVIC) for Iraq, presented a report to the
United Nations Thursday, mapping out a blueprint for the staff
structure of the new U.N. arms regime.
</P>
<P>
UNMOVIC was created by Security Council Resolution 1284 adopted
last December to replace now defunct the United Nations Special
Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of dismantling Iraq's weapons of
mass destruction and resume the U.N.arms inspection in Iraq which
has been suspended since the U.S-led military strikes against the
country in December 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to Blix's plan, there will be no deputy post for
UNMOVIC, but an executive assistant with less power will be set up,
a contrast with UNSCOM which was headed by Richard Butler.
</P>
<P>
The deputy post of UNSCOM has been transitionally held by an
American. The last one was Charles Duelfer who reigned in February
after the establishment of UNMOVIC.
</P>
<P>
Unlike UNSCOM, Blix recommended in the plan that UNMOVIC will
be strong on experts and technical personnel rather than political
functionaries. He also proposed two-step approach to recruitment
of the personnel for the arms regime, with most UNMOVIC staff
being U.N. employees.
</P>
<P>
UNSCOM relied mainly on experts picked up and paid by their
government, a practice resulted in the alleged UNSCOM's spying for
the United States which led to the demise of UNSCOM.
</P>
<P>
Blix wants his arms staff to firmly act with a clear U.N.
identity and to avoid them from getting orders from outside the U.
N.body.
</P>
<P>
Blix also wants his arms regime to be tightly-controlled and
leakproof, saying the low of intelligence must be one way.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that agency's public information officer will
ensure that there will be a single authoritative point of contact
with the media, Blix himself or someone gets authorization from
him.
</P>
<P>
He noted that UNMOVIC has the same rights of UNSCOM, with the
freedom of movement and immediate, unrestricted access to any and
all areas, facilities, equipment, records and means of
transportation.
</P>
<P>
But he proposed to open a cultural program for his arms staff
which is aimed to train them in importance of understanding
national sensitivities and the proper handling of adversarial
situation in the field.
</P>
<P>
This is what UNSCOM failed in its operation and this is also
what led to consequent confrontations between the U.N. arms
inspectors and Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The proposed plan is an apparent bid of Blix to motivate Iraq
to cooperate with the United Nations and allow the return of the U.
N. arms inspectors.
</P>
<P>
Once the plan is approved by the 15-member Security Council,
possibly next week, the next step will be a visit to Iraq. But so
far, Iraq has reiterated that it banns U.N.arms inspectors from
returning unless the sanctions against the country get lifted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment in Switzerland Falls to Lowest Since 1992 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment in Switzerland has
fallen to its lowest level since 1992, the economic ministry
announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The economic ministry said that the rate fell last month from 2.
4 percent in February to 2.3 percent, with white-collar industry
showing the biggest growth. The employment office in the ministry'
s state secretariat said it now expects the average for this year
to drop to two percent, 0.3 percent below its earlier forecasts.
</P>
<P>
"All economic indicators point upwards," said Jean-Luc Nordmann,
head of the office, "We are on the way to full employment."
</P>
<P>
He said that some branches of industry were now having
difficulty
finding workers. The number of people looking for jobs fell nearly
8,000 to 140,000 in March, while the number of employment
vacancies rose slightly to 15,000.
</P>
<P>
However, unemployment rates continue to differ greatly between
regions, particularly between German and French-speaking cantons.
They averaged about 0.5 percent in parts of central and eastern
Switzerland last month, but reached 4.5 in canton Geneva and 3.7
in Italian-speaking canton Ticino. The biggest drop was recorded
in canton Valais, where it fell more than one percent to 2.6
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
