<HEADLINE> Romanian Government Team to Survey Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Prime Minister Mugur
Isarescu on Friday disposed the formation of a government
commission that will travel at weekend to the counties affected
recently by bad weather.
</P>
<P>
The flood-stricken areas will be visited by representatives of
the National Defence Ministry, the Interior Ministry, the Ministry
of Public Works and Physical Planning and the Ministry of Waters,
Forestry and Environment Protection, headed by Defence Minister
Sorin Frunzaverde, who is also vice-president of the Government
Commission of Protection Against Disasters.
</P>
<P>
The Commission will analyze the situation in the counties of
Caras Severin, Hunedoara, Timis, Alba, Sibiu and Arad, in central
and western Romania.
</P>
<P>
Floods affected 12 counties, including Alba, Caras-Severin,
Arad,Bihor and Hunedoara which are worst hit. All in all 308
localities were inundated, 43 of which are isolated as bridges
were damaged.
</P>
<P>
Two people are reported missing and three dead, 2,443 homes
were damaged, 97 localities are cut off the electricity supply and
13 off water supply. Farmland totalling 29,267 hectares were
flooded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
