<HEADLINE> Canada's Jobless Rate Reamins at 6.8 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Canada's jobless rate remained at 6.
8 percent in March, unchanged from that of the previous month,
Statistic Canada reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth straight month for the country to record the
lowest unemployment for the past 24 years.
</P>
<P>
Up to 30,000 full-time positions were created last month as a
result of the strengthening Canadian economy, which has led to a 3.
2 percent rise in the overall employment over the past year,
according to the official statistical agency.
</P>
<P>
Although the job creation is absorbed by a growing number of
people seeking for better positions, the country's influential
economists forecast an even lower jobless rate of 6 percent by the
end of the year to further reduce unemployment from last month's 1.
1 million people.
</P>
<P>
The country's economy will advance by 4.4 percent in terms of
gross domestic product this year, outperforming all other G-7
countries except the U.S., the Bank of Nova Scotia predicted last
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
