<HEADLINE> Cyclone Hudah Brings Heavy Rains to Mozambican Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Cyclone Hudah has continued to
cause heavy rains in coastal districts of central Mozambique, but
so far the centre of the cyclone remains in the Mozambique
Channel.
</P>
<P>
According to Radio Mozambique, torrential rains have hit
Quelimane, capital of Zambezia Province, and the districts of
Pebane and Maganja da Costa.
</P>
<P>
The Zambezia provincial government is to send a team to these
two districts on Saturday to investigate the extent of the damage.
</P>
<P>
As the cyclone approaches land, more heavy rain is expected.
</P>
<P>
The cyclone is moving south-southwest, and on this course it
may well strike the central port city of Beira, which also
suffered badly from cyclone Eline in February. 
</P>
