<HEADLINE> China Refutes Taiwan Separatist's Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Spokesmen for both China's Taiwan
Affairs Office of the State Council and Taiwan Work Office of the
Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party issued a joint
statement today to criticize Annette Lu's remarks on "Taiwan
independence."
</P>
<P>
They said Lu's remarks during an interview with a Hong Kong
media organ has challenged the One China policy and has provoked
animosity between the people on both sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
This shows that Lu is an "extremist and typical 'Taiwan
independence' element," they said.
</P>
<P>
Her remarks put a gloss on Japan's occupation of Taiwan, thus
deeply hurting the feelings and national pride of the Chinese
people, they added.
</P>
<P>
"In fact, she has become a scum of the Chinese nation," they
emphasized.
</P>
<P>
The people of Taiwan are Chinese. This is a hard fact. No
matter who becomes the leader of Taiwan, the fact that Taiwan is a
part of China can never be changed, they stressed.
</P>
<P>
"We will fight to the end against whoever sticks to the
position of 'two states' and 'Taiwan independence'", they said.
</P>
<P>
Anyone who advocates national separatism is doomed to failure,
they concluded. 
</P>
