<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ARATS Refutes Annette Lu's Separatist Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the mainland-based
Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits today pointed
out that Annette Lu's recent statements have exposed the
disgraceful face of a small group of "Taiwan independence"
advocates.
</P>
<P>
He said that their aim is to split China, and they have
maliciously attacked the mainland as well as all the Chinese
people. There is no doubt that their schemes backfire.
</P>
<P>
He said that the basis and prerequisite for the development of
relations across the Taiwan Straits are the One China principle.
However, Lu insists that the principle is creating a "threat" to
Taiwan, and people who agree with the principle are "surrendering"
to the mainland.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Lu is merely spreading rumors and vilifying
the development of the cross-Straits relations and dialogues, and
her goal is to instigate the Taiwan people to oppose the One China
principle.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Lu's statements that "Taiwan respects
China" and it "will not offend China" reveal that she totally
denies the fact that Taiwan is part of China, and denies the
agreement that "both sides across the Taiwan Straits adhere to the
One China principle".
</P>
<P>
Moreover, she has vilified the Chinese people's will to
safeguard state sovereignty and territorial integrity, and bruised
the aspiration shared by the Chinese people worldwide who hope to
see the reunification of China and national unity.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Lu's "friendship" and "kindness" are nothing but
deception.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman stressed that any issue can be discussed on the
basis of the One China principle. Cross-straits dialogues and
negotiations can be carried out only if this principle and the
fact that Taiwan is part of China are recognized, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
