<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0041 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Releases Latest Foreign Currency Assets Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 7 (Xinhua) - The Hong Kong Monetary Authority
(HKMA) announced here Friday that the official foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong amounted to 93.8 billion U.S. dollars at the
end of March 2000.
</P>
<P>
Including unsettled forward contracts, the foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong at the end of March 2000 stood at 93.9 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In terms of foreign currency reserves ranking, Hong Kong is the
world's fourth largest holder of foreign currency reserves after
Japan, China's mainland and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets of 93.8 billion U.S. dollars
represent over seven times the currency in circulation or about 39
percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
