<HEADLINE> Rainstorms Hit Romania, Several People Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains and a sharp rise in
the temperature over the week have caused a rapid snow thaw,
making rivers overflow and inundate 60 villages and towns in
central and western Romania.
</P>
<P>
Several people were reported missing.
</P>
<P>
Over 200 homesteads and hundreds of hectares of farmland were
submerged under water in Hunedoara county, central Romania, while
water blocked main roads in the adjoining Alba county.
</P>
<P>
Flash floods swept through a village in the western Timis
county, where a family was announced missing.
</P>
<P>
Fifty villages in Arad county, which abuts on Timis county in
the north, were blacked out by strong gusts of wind. Railroad
traffic in southeastern Romania, near the Black Sea, has been
affected.
</P>
<P>
Military men moved in to take stranded families to safety.
</P>
<P>
The heaviest rains were registered at Moneasa, in central
Romania, and weathermen forecast no let-up in rainfalls in the
next few hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
