<HEADLINE> China's Former Olympic Champion Diver Wins at Nationals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, North China, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China's former world
champion and Olympic gold medalist Fu Mingxia won the women's
three-meter springboard synchronized diving event at the national
championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A super-star with numerous titles from such world-class events
as Olympic Games, world championships and World Cup meets, Fu
teamed with Guo Jingjing from Hebei Province on Friday to take the
national title with 318.30 points.
</P>
<P>
"There is still room to improve in our performance," Fu
admitted after her victory. "We had only less a month for joint
training before the championships," she added.
</P>
<P>
A a student of economic management in the famed Beijing-based
Qinghua University, she resumed regular training last year as a
member of the University's team.
</P>
<P>
Guo Jingjing also outscored others to take the women's one-
meter springboard title, with 286.95 points. The teenager is
widely thought to be one of China's Olympic medal hopefuls for the
Sydney Games.
</P>
<P>
The national championships also serve as the country's Olympic
qualifying tournament. 
