<HEADLINE> Mozambique Coast Areas Hit by Storms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Strong winds and rains caused by
cyclone Hudah have hit the coastal districts of the northern
province of Nampula, Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
However, instead of coming inland, the cyclone changed its
course and has been moving slowly down the Mozambique Channel, the
Mozambique News Agency reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
But Hudah appears to be losing intensity. The wind speed has
fallen from 100 to 30 or 40 kilometers an hour.
</P>
<P>
According to Nampula provincial governor Rosario Mualeia, Moma
district was the area worst affected by the rains and winds caused
by the cyclone.
</P>
<P>
One child is said to have died in Moma, though the
circumstances of this death were not reported.
</P>
<P>
Flimsy houses in Moma were blown down by the winds, and an
unspecified number of people rendered homeless. Extensive areas of
maize and cassava fields were damaged.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-five military campaign tents are on hand in Nampula City
to provide temporary shelter for the homeless, Mualeia said,
adding that food aid, in the shape of 250 tons of maize and
enriched biscuits, is also immediately available. 
</P>
</TEXT>
