<HEADLINE> 9 Killed in Traffic Accidents in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and three
others injured in two separate traffic accidents in Greece Friday.
</P>
<P>
Early Friday, a car collided with a truck with Albanian license
plates on the Antirio-Ioannina national highway near the
northwestern Greek town of Agrinion, and both vehicles burst into
flames as the car smashed on the truck's gas tank, the semi-
official Athens News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Eight people, including the car's driver and three children
were burned to death, and police said that all the eight people
were believed to be illegal Iraqi Immigrants.
</P>
<P>
In the Koropi region of eastern Attica, a 20-year-old conscript
was killed and three teens injured early Friday after two cars
collided.
</P>
<P>
Greece's traffic accident rate is among the highest in the 15-
member European Union countries, with more than 2,000 people
killed and 30,000 others injured annually in accidents. 
