<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece's Inflation Rises in March  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Greece's inflation rose to 3.1
percent in March from February's 2.9 percent, the National
Statistics Service (NSS) announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NSS attributed the increase in inflation to a 4.0 percent
rise in durable household items and services, a 13.9 percent jump
in clothing-footwear and a 2.5 percent increase in transport
prices.
</P>
<P>
The country's inflation is expected to be stable or slightly
drop in the following two months due to the seasonal exclusion of
the heating oil index from the consumer price index (CPI) basket
and other factors.
</P>
<P>
It is also expected that the country's harmonized consumer
price index, which is used to compare Greek inflation with that of
other European Union members, will remain at 2.0 in March.
</P>
</TEXT>
