<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Draws Kazakhstan in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong, China, was held to a
1-1 draw by Kazakhstan in the opening day of the play-off of the
2000 Asia/Oceania Zone Group II for the Davis Cup tennis
tournament here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, China, beaten by Pakistan 3-2 in February in the
first round of the Group, took the lead in the opening singles
when their No.1 player Melvin Tong came from one set behind to win
three straight sets to overwhelm Kazakhstan's No. 2 Pavel Baranov
3-6, 6-3, 6-4 and 7-5.
</P>
<P>
The following singles saw a clash between two teenagers -- Hong
Kong's number two Wayne Wong and Kazakhstan's ace player Alexei
Kedruyk.
</P>
<P>
A big server, Kedruyk proved too powerful both at net and
baseline for his opponent, winning the match with an ease score of
6-2, 6-2 and 6-2.
</P>
<P>
"The decider of the whole match is going to depend on the
result of the doubles on Saturday," said Xia Jiaping, coach of the
Hong Kong, China team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
