<HEADLINE> Canada Beats Sweden in Women's Ice Hockey World Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Canada beat Sweden 4-0 Thursday in
their final game of the round-robin play of the women's world ice
hockey championship at Mississauga's Hershey Centre, Ontario.
</P>
<P>
In a game that attracted a near-capacity crowd of 4,479, Canada
had to take a tough challenge from the huge Swedes.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian women put constant pressure on Swedish goalie
Lotta Gothesson. She was confronted with 44 shots whileas her
Canadian counterpart Sami Jo Small took just eight, the fewest so
far by a Canadian opponent in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
In another game Thursday, the Americans finished the round-
robin play with a 4-3 win over the Finns.
</P>
<P>
Canada, which won all their three games by an aggregate score
of 21-1, will face Finland in the semi-finals on Saturday. The U.
S. team will take on Sweden in the other semi-final.
</P>
<P>
In earlier games of the championship which opened on Monday,
Canada beatJapan 9-0 and won over China 8-1. The Amercians
trounced Germany 16-1 and downed Russia 15-0.
</P>
<P>
Medal play seems another Canada-U.S. showdown on Sunday.
Canada downed the United States 3-1 last year in Espoo, Finland,
to win gold for the fifth consecutive time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
