<HEADLINE> Thailand Big Winners at Olympic Boxing Asian Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The qualifying tournament, which is the third and last leg of
Asia's qualifying tournament for Olympics 2000, concluded with the
last 28 Olympic tickets to the Sydney event shared by boxers from
12 Asian countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
With five boxers who had made their way to Sydney in the two
earlier legs, Thailand now has boxers in nine small and medium
categories among a total of 12 categories.
</P>
<P>
But it still lagged behind Uzbekistan, which has qualified 10
boxers for Sydney.
</P>
<P>
South Korea are eligible to send nine boxers to the Games while
Kazakhstan has seven qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
Kyrgyzstan and Iran have five boxers each qualified for the
final games of the Olympics while China, India, Pakistan and the
Philippines have four each.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the total 70 tickets were shared by Syria, Japan,
Indonesia, Mongolia and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
</P>
</TEXT>
