<HEADLINE> China, US Hold Seminar on Psychopathy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Experts from China and the United
States opened a seminar on psychopathy and its influence on people
here today.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time for psychiatrists from the two
countries to hold a seminar. The last one was held in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Some 500 psychiatrists attended the meeting, featuring hot
issues such as suicide, melancholia and children's mental problems.
</P>
<P>
Psychopathy is said to be a major problem in China nowadays.
Half of the deaths of people between the ages of 15 and 35 are
suicides.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will discuss new methods of curing psychopathy,
including gene therapy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
