<HEADLINE> Philippine Govt Studying Proposal to Limit Holidays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government is now
carefully studying suggestions from some sectors to limit the
number of non-working holidays observed in the country.
</P>
<P>
Secretary Bienvenido Laguesma of the Department of Labor and
Employment (DOLE) said Friday the suggestions stemmed from
concerns that too many holidays may adversely affect the
productivity of workers.
</P>
<P>
"We are looking into these suggestions. We want to look closely
at the productivity aspect and its implication on our workers,"
Laguesma said in a radio interview.
</P>
<P>
The DOLE is also encouraging labor groups and employers to meet
halfway and work out an acceptable compromise on the matter, the
secretary said.
</P>
<P>
Laguesma said limiting the number of holidays may contribute to
efforts to attract investments and generate job opportunities,
pointing out that the government wants to create enough employment
opportunities at home for Filipinos so that they need not seek
greener pastures abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
