<HEADLINE> Manila to Help Rebels Prepare Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government said
Friday that it fully supports the plan of the rebel Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) to prepare a comprehensive action plan for
the development of Muslim Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Aventajado, chairman of the Presidential Committee on
Flagship Programs and Projects, made the announcement during a
press conference at the Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
Aventajado was accompanied at the press conference by Saeed Ali
Daof, emissary extraordinary and plenipotentiary of MILF chief
Hashim Salamat.
</P>
<P>
President Joseph Estrada designated Aventajado as his personal
representative to discuss, assist and work with the Economic
Development Committee of the MILF in the development of their
plans and programs for Muslim Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
This includes the preparation of the action plan and
feasibility studies and the conversion of MILF camps into MILF
special economic zones but subject to the provisions of law.
</P>
<P>
Aventajado also pointed out that President Estrada believes
that the programs to develop the MILF-controlled areas will not
only enhance the confidence-building measures but will also
improve the lives and well-being of "our Muslim brothers and
sisters."
</P>
<P>
For his part, Daof stressed that the MILF action plan covers
specific development and livelihood projects which are supportive
of the government's flagship and other projects.
</P>
<P>
He said that MILF projects would serve as "realistic and
practical building mechanisms" not only for the people of Mindanao
but also for the Estrada administration and the MILF leadership as
well.
</P>
<P>
The MILF has been fighting for an independent state in the
Muslim Mindanao during the past two decades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
