<HEADLINE> South Korean Oil Imports Influence Trade Surplus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 7 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's oil imports in the
first quarter of this year hit 6.1 billion U.S. dollars, up 3.5
billion dollars or 57 percent over a year ago, denting its trade
surplus.
</P>
<P>
The trade surplus fell to 3.94 billion dollars as a result of
the increase, said the South Korean Commerce, Industry and Energy
Ministry Friday.
</P>
<P>
South Korean customs-based trade surplus in the first three
months of this year only amounted to 750 million dollars, down 3.
94 billion dollars from 4.69 billion dollars in the same time last
year.
</P>
<P>
The country's oil imports in January reached 2.15 billion
dollars, 1.88 billion dollars in February and 2.1 billion dollars
in March. 
</P>
