<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Riot Rocks Southern French Town  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A riot by teenagers has rocked a
southern French town for two nights after police seized a large
amount of hashish in a "sensitive" district, press reports here
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Groups of teenagers have been fighting some 150 police in the
town of Berthe de la Seyne-sur-Mer in the department of Var,
southern France, where racial tension between the French and Arab
and Black immigrant communities is always high.
</P>
<P>
French officials and press usually call the places a "sensitive
area" with high unemployment rate, high poverty rate and distinct
immigrant population.
</P>
<P>
A 41-year-old mother of five children killed herself after
police seized from her home 3.5 kilograms of hashish, a drug
widely smoked but banned in France.
</P>
<P>
Angry youths threw self-made Molotov cocktails at police and
burnt several cars after the mother died, reported Agence France-
Presse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
