the average in March, before falling to 1.39 dollars by September.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal
</P>
<P>
-- Celera completed a major step toward deciphering the entire
human genetic blueprint. The U.S. biotech company said it
sequenced 99% of all the human genetic material in seven months,
and will now try to figure out how the DNA fragments fit together
to form the human genome. Celera shares surged 20% to 137 dollars
on the news; other genomics stocks rallied.
</P>
<P>
-- Nato troops in Kosovo wounded a Serb when they fired on a
crowd outside a monastery where moderate Serbs had fled to escape
retribution for joining a multiethnic governing body. In Serbia,
fire destroyed an independent broadcast facility.  
