<HEADLINE> Austrian Businesses Eye Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian Federal Chamber of
Commerce is planning to set up more representative offices in
China, the Chamber's president Leopold Maderthaner said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We see great potential for cooperation with China, and we
should accelerate our efforts to seek cooperation opportunities,"
said Maderthaner, who is on his seventh visit to China.
</P>
<P>
He was leading an Austrian economic delegation to this capital
city of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
He said every time he comes to China he sees that great changes
have taken in the country.
</P>
<P>
Representing the interests of Austria's 300,000 enterprises,
the Austrian Federal Chamber of Commerce has established four
representative offices in China since 1994.
</P>
<P>
They are in Shanghai, Shenyang, Chongqing and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that more Austrian enterprises would
seize this great opportunity and invest in China.
</P>
<P>
For this purpose, his chamber plans to send five more national
economic delegations to China this year, starting in May.
</P>
<P>
According to Maderthaner, 85 Austrian companies have set up
representative offices in China, and more than 90 Austrian
patented techologies have found Chinese cooperation partners.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chinese businesses have also increased cooperation
with their Austrian counterparts. The Austrian Federal Chamber of
Commerce received 42 visiting Chinese delegations last year.
</P>
