<HEADLINE> PLA Doctors Make Artificial Bones, Membranes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Doctors serving in the People's
Liberation Army (PLA) have invented artificial bones and membranes,
in cooperation with scientists from Anhui University, according to
the China Defense News.
</P>
<P>
The artificial bones and membranes can be used for emergency
operations, chiefly by the army for injuries sustained by soldiers
on the battlefield or in training. They are made of a new material
which has none of the side-effects associated with traditional
types of artificial bones and membranes. In addition, they have
the functions of stopping bleeding and promoting the rapid
restoration of injured tissues.
</P>
<P>
The new inventions, which have already been patented,are easy
to make, store and carry. 
