<HEADLINE> Scholars Meet to Discuss Yan'an Spirit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The China Yan'an Spirit Research
Society and "Modern Shaanxi" magazine have jointly held a forum
here to mark the 10th anniversary of President Jiang Zemin's
inscription reading "The Yan'an Spirit Will Shine For Ever".
</P>
<P>
Yan'an, in northwestern China's Shaanxi Province, was the
headquarters of the Communist Party of China (CPC) during the war
against Japanese aggression in the 1930s and 1940s.
</P>
<P>
The participants were of the unanimous opinion that the Yan'an
Spirit, part of Mao Zedong Thought, is a great ideological legacy
for the CPC, and that Jiang's inscription indicates that the third-
generation leadership attaches great importance to inheriting and
displaying the Yan'an Spirit.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's inscription is an important summing-up of the Party's
historic experience and a call for the whole Party to continue
displaying the Yan'an Spirit, they held. 
</P>
