<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Highlights Industrial Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo has said
that China is facing a serious situation as far as industrial
safety and preventing industrial accidents are concerned.
</P>
<P>
He urged local governments, departments and units to join hands
to detect hidden dangers and strengthen management to prevent
major accidents, ensure the safety of life and properties, and
create a sound social environment for pushing forward the reform,
opening up and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier made the remarks at a teleconference here
today on industrial safety, which was presided over by State
Councilor Luo Gan.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that since 1999 a number of major industrial accidents
have occurred, drawing great attention from the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the accidents to ignorance of the concerned laws
and regulations as well as corruption in some localities,
departments and units. It is high time to deal with these problems,
he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Complete checks should be done in all sectors, especially in
industries and places where poisonous, combustible and explosive
materials and equipment are in use or stored nearby, according to
the official.
</P>
<P>
Those responsible for major accidents must be severely punished
or disciplined in accordance with the law, while the results of
handling these cases should be made public and put under the
supervision of the people, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
