<HEADLINE> Singapore Share Prices Close 1.8 percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed higher on
Singapore Stock Market Friday boosted by local technology counters
and the overnight rally on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index ended 39.00 points higher, or
1.8 percent, to close at 2,150.51 points in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
Total volume stood at 390.78 million shares worth 786.54
million Singapore dollars (459.94 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
led losers by 167 to 142 with 219 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
LafeTech topped the actives chart as it registered a turnover
of 75.88 million units on 0.41 Singapore dollars per share. The
second largest block was the 54.66 million parcel by JurTech which
was transacted at 0.34 Singapore dollars per issue. It was
followed by Brierley which had 13.84 million counters changing
hand.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led gainers of the day shooting up 360 cents to
close at 51.30 Singapore dollars. Venture surged up 180 cents to
finish at 24.00 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 moved up 140 cents to
end at 30.40 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
SIA continued to top the losers of the day shedding 30 cents to
close at 15.00 Singapore dollars. Global Tech, KepCorp and Seaview
each fell by 20 cents to finish at 2.60, 4.02 and 8.60 Singapore
dollars respectively. CityDev lose 15 cents to end at 8.00
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that market sentiment was supported by the
recovery on Wall Street overnight and expectations that SPH (
Singapore Press Holding) will announce higher earnings when it
released its results Friday.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the rise of SngTel shares, after the company's
announcement of its entry into Malaysia via a stake in Time
Engineering, also helped to lift the market.  
</P>
