<HEADLINE> World Health Day Observed in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Day is being
observed Friday throughout Bangladesh with this year's theme of "
Safe Blood Starts with me -- Blood Saves Lives."
</P>
<P>
In a message on the occasion, Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin
Ahmed urged all adult people of the country to donate blood at
least once a year to save lives of dying people.
</P>
<P>
In her message, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina called for
developing health awareness to reduce health problems and minimize
child and mother mortality.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health and Family Welfare is formulating a new
draft law to prevent commercial blood donation by professional
blood donors in the country, Minister for Health and Family
Welfare Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim told a press conference Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said plans to set up blood banks in the country's 97
hospitals have got underway to ensure safe blood transfusion.
</P>
<P>
Steps are being taken to train the doctors and paramedics to
ensure safe blood collection, appropriate screening of donors,
proper storage and appropriate clinical use of blood, Selim said.
</P>
<P>
Selim said the Bangladesh Red Crescent Society will soon set up
five modern blood banks in the divisional headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
