<HEADLINE> 33 Rebels killed in Fighting in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 33 Tamil rebels were
killed Thursday in fierce fighting in the north of Sri Lanka, a
military spokesman said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman F.P. Witana said government troops continued to
advance from their earlier held positions in Muhamalai.
</P>
<P>
The army's artillery fire inflicted heavy casualties on the
rebels, killing 14 rebels and wounding about 60 others, he said.
Seven soldiers were wounded in the fighting.
</P>
<P>
Witana said troops killed at least three rebels and injured
three others in Aarialai Tongue. And the army killed six rebels in
an area south of Nagar Kovil.
</P>
<P>
Witana added that government troops also killed 10 Tamil rebels
in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels, who have been fighting a war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country since 1983, have intensified their offensives over the
last 10 days in a bid to retake their former stronghold of Jaffna
Peninsula. Hundreds of rebels and government soldiers have been
killed or injured during the period. 
</P>
