<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Weekly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market showed
signs of minor advance in the past week following the downtrend of
recent weeks, the Financial Weekly newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the bourse registered weekly gains of 3.05 percent when
it closed on Thursday at 481.92 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover for the week reached 102.5 million Cyprus
pounds (174.3 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The average daily volume of trade reached 20.5 million pounds
(34.9 million dollars), down by 0.6 million pounds (1 million
dollars) or 0.6 percent from last week.
</P>
<P>
All sectors except the industrial and insurance sectors posted
healthy gains, with tourism sector took the lead as it registered
weekly gains of 8.55 percent.  
</P>
