<HEADLINE> Thailand, Vietnam to Sign Cooperation deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Vietnam have agreed
to step up bilateral cooperation to promote travel and tourism
between them as well as within the Greater Mekong Sub-region,
local sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
A deal to this effect was struck at a recent meeting in Bangkok
by Paveena Hongsakula, minister to the Prime's Minister Office,
and Vietnamese Vice President Nguyen Thi Binh.
</P>
<P>
The two countries agreed to promote bilateral tourism and
develop the essential infrastructure important to the development
of the travel and tourism industry in the region, such as
convenient transportation links, communications and human
resources.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will exchange official visits designed to share
expertise, promote investment, and undertake joint marketing and
promotion strategies. Attention will focus on development of the
air and land links between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
