<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Suggests New Approach of Aiding Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- France has suggested a "new approach
" of providing financial aid to Russia by the West after summing
up the balance sheet of cooperation between Russia and the West
over the past 10 years.
</P>
<P>
French Finance Minister Laurent Fabius and Foreign Minister
Hubert Vedrine made the proposal in a letter to the European Union
and other members of the Group of Eight most industrialized
nations after the election of Vladimir Putin as Russian president,
the daily Le Figaro reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers said that despite the dispute between the
West and Russia over Chechnya, the West should continue to provide
aid to Moscow in the long term, said the report.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue to help Russia, but the problem is for what
and how?" the two ministers were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that the West should be "more demanding" in
imposing the conditions for cooperation. "The legal and judicial
cooperation should make up the first priority," they said.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also said that the amount of the money which
was brought out of Russia by "the mafias and the oligarchy"
surpassed that of international aid sent in over the past 10 years.
</P>
</TEXT>
