<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Sharply Up on Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed sharply
up today following the overnight rally on the Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip Hang Seng Index (HSI) jumped 450.29 points, or 2.
73 percent, to close at 16,941.68 points on a turnover of 13.371
billion HK dollars (1.71 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Technology stocks, which had dragged down the index earlier in
the week, rebounded sharply on the rise of New York's Nasdaq
composite index, which shot 2.36 percent, or 98.34 points, to
close Thursday's trading at 4,267.56 points.
</P>
<P>
Market heavyweight China Telecom (Hong Kong) Ltd. soared 6.5 HK
dollars, or 10.36 percent, to close at 69.25 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
