26 percent and 0.52 percent respectively while Utilities and
Commerce &AMP; Industry gained 1.51 percent and 5.43 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng China Enterprises rose 2.52 percent, or 9 points, to
close at 346.28 points while Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index rocketed 8.95 percent, or 122 points, to close
at 1,480.06 points.
</P>
<P>
HSI rose 1.01 percent, or 166.45 to open the morning session at
16,657.84. It soared 2.26 percent, or 372.61 points to close the
morning session at 16,864.00.  
