<HEADLINE> Thai Parties Committed to Friendly Relationship with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) left here Friday for home after winning major
Thai parties' commitment to developing friendly relationship with
China.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of all these parties who held talks with the delegation
promised that whichever party in Thailand assumes the reins of
government, it will always follow the policy of developing
friendly relationship with China, an informed source told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
They expressed the belief that the strengthening of party-to-
party relations between the two countries will help develop
bilateral ties in an all-around way, the source said.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by Dai Bingguo, a member of the CPC Central
Committee and head of the International Liaison Department of the
CPC Central Committee, arrived here on Monday for a five-day visit
at the invitation of Surin Pitsuwan, a member of the Executive
Committee of the ruling Democrat Party and Thai foreign minister,
after visiting India and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
During the visit here, the delegation met Prime Minister Chuan
Leekpai, who is also Democrat leader, Surin Pitsuwan, deputy
Democrat leader Banyat Bantadtan, Chart Thai leader Banharn Silpa-
archa, Chart Pattana leader Korn Dabbaransi, opposition leader and
New Aspiration leader Chavalit Yongchaiyudh and deputy Thai Rak
Thai leader Pitak Intrawityanunt.
</P>
<P>
The visit by the CPC delegation aimed at enhancing relations
between the CPC and local political parties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
