<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newspaper Says British Economy on Track to Join Euro Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Britain could join the European
single currency "in the near future" because the economy has
already converged with those of the 11 countries in the euro-zone,
according to a newspaper report on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper Independent said officials in the House of
Commons (lower house of the parliament) have agreed to an
independent analysis which suggests that Britain might be able to
join the euro in the near future if it chooses to.
</P>
<P>
The unpublished report comes as the British government is under
growing pressure to make a firm statement of intent to join the
euro to bring down the overvalued pound, the Independent said.
</P>
<P>
"If the United Kingdom government decided in the near future to
recommend entry it could do so with a set of economic indicators
that, with the exception of the exchange rate, would almost
certainly pass any reasonable convergence assessment process," the
newspaper quoted the Commons report as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the report, compiled by the House of Commons Library,
admits the exchange rate remains "the issue" to be settled before
a possible entry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
