<HEADLINE> CAPOF Delegation Wraps up Sichuan Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A delegation from the China
Association for Promoting Overseas Friendship, headed by Wang
Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), has ended
their visit in Sichuan Province and left for Chongqing
Municipality today.
</P>
<P>
While in Sichuan, the delegation, composed of 156 members from
Australia, New Zealand, Hong Kong, and Macao, inspected natural
resources in the cities of Chengdu, Leshan, and Emei and visited
several enterprises funded by overseas Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zhongwei, the governor of Sichuan Province, briefed
members of the delegation on the investment environment,
government investment policies, and development prospects of
Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo said China's strategy of speeding up economic
development in western China has won support from Chinese of all
walks of life overseas, and they should gain a better
understanding of conditions there before making investment plans.
