<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Housing Loan Not Enough: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Individual housing loans in 1999
is quite small in size compared with the country's total
outstanding loans, experts said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, individual housing loans amounted to
126 billion yuan. Total outstanding loan stood at 9.4 trillion and
GDP at 8.2 trillion. The proportion of housing loan against total
loans was 1.5 percent, far lower than the general 30 percent in
other countries, "China Securities" said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from changing people's spending habits, better financial
services must be introduced to help increase housing loans,
according to Xie Jiajin, director of Housing and Real Estate
Department in the Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
Xie called for simplified procedures in loan application and
introduction of insurance and guarantee policies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
