<HEADLINE> China to Send Large Delegation to Int'l Agro-Foodtech Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of
Agriculture will send a large delegation to the International Agro-
Foodtech Exposition to be held in Beijing from April 11 to 14 to
trade high-tech products and attract foreign investment, a
ministry official said today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation consists of China's top agricultural trade and
research institutions including the ministry's Foreign Economic
Cooperation Center, the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences
and the Chinese University of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The Expo will showcase the most recent high-tech achievements
and products from major Chinese agriculture research institutions
and companies.
</P>
<P>
During the Expo, a seminar on major Chinese agricultural high-
tech projects will be held to publicize information and serve as a
bridge between traders and researchers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a high-profile seminar on China's agriculture will
also be held with officials and experts from Chinese and foreign
government departments as well as companies. The seminar will
address such topics as China's agriculture after joining the World
Trade Organization and the prospects of investment in China's
agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
The Agro-Foodtech Exposition is jointly sponsored by the
Specialized Sub-Council of Agriculture under the China Council for
the Promotion of International Trade and a French exhibition
company. More than 300 companies from 17 countries and regions
will attend.  
</P>
