<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hi-Tech Exports Show Good Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China's exports of high-tech
products during the first two months this year reached 3.95
billion U.S. dollars, a rise of 48.2 percent over the same period
last year, and seven points higher than the average growth rate of
the country's exports as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to a series of policies favoring high-tech product
exports, these products accounted for 12.5 percent of all exports
in the first two months.
</P>
<P>
Exports of computers and communications technologies topped 2.9
billion U.S. dollars, ranking first in terms of volume among high-
tech exports, and electronic technology ranked second with 620
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports of material technology showed the strongest momentum,
rising 95.5 percent over the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, high-tech imports stood at 6.04
billion U.S. dollars for the first two months, a rise of 47.7
percent on a yearly-basis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
