<HEADLINE> Beijing Youth Discuss Former Soviet Union Hero </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Beijing members of the Communist
Youth League of China gathered here today to discuss Pavel
Korqagin, the hero of a former Soviet Union novel "The Making of A
Hero".
</P>
<P>
The 20-episode TV adaptation of the novel was shown on China's
Central TV Station. The protagonist of the Ukrainian novel by
Nikolai Alexiviq Ostrovsky (1904-1936) grows up in poverty and
becomes a devoting revolutionary in the early years of the former
Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
Former students from the "Pavel Class" in the fifties attended
today's discussion. Sun Guiying said that Pavel is an outstanding
member of the Communist Youth League. His spirit is enterprising,
indomitable and optimistic and still inspires young people today.
</P>
<P>
Students from Qinghua University expressed their determination
to learn from Pavel and attune personal aspirations to the country
's development.
</P>
<P>
The TV serial was aired in February with an audience rating of
more than 60 percent. It was shown again beginning last week.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Youth Daily even offered special columns for the
discussion: "Pavel and Bill Gates: Who is the Hero."
</P>
<P>
The novel has become a bestseller around the country.  
</P>
