<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Picasso's Oil Painting on Display in Auckland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Pablo Picasso's oil painting,
Verre et pichet (glass and pitcher) was unveiled at the Simpson
Grierson Season launched by the Auckland Art Gallery Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Television New Zealand, it is the first
Picasso oil painting to enter a New Zealand public collection and
the first time this work has ever been shown in public.
</P>
<P>
Picasso painted Verre et pichet in 1944 during the Battle of
Paris. It is placed alongside works by other artists who make
personal or political statements about the experience and cruelty
of war.
</P>
<P>
The Simpson Grierson Season, which showcases New Zealand's
finest art collection, runs from April until October 2000. The
works it displays span 700 years of European art as well as
drawing on art from the United States, Australia and New Zealand (
including works by Maori and Pacific artists).
</P>
<P>
The Picasso oil painting Verre et pichet was recently acquired
by the Auckland Art Gallery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
