<HEADLINE> 3 Women Killed in Manila Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Three Filipino women were killed
when a nine-hour fire struck a shopping center in Makati City of
Metro Manila from Thursday night to Friday morning, police said.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigations showed that the fire which hit the ABC
Mall was caused by an electrical short-circuit and it spread after
an explosion.
</P>
<P>
The charred bodies of the three women, all residents of Metro
Manila, were found by firemen who checked the debris after the
fire, police said.
</P>
<P>
The women, who were exercising inside the Trace Gym of the mall,
failed to escape from the burning gym as the fire exit was closed
during the fire. 
</P>
