<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Urges Vigilance Against Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
has ordered security agencies in the country to be alert to
prevent any terrorist attack like the August 1998 bombing from
reoccurring.
</P>
<P>
The security team should be vigilant, especially on
non-governmental organizations, which could be used as conduits to
bring in people to do harm to Kenya, he was quoted by Friday's
Daily Nation newspaper as saying.
</P>
<P>
Officially commencing the construction of the August 7 Memorial
Park on the former American embassy site on Thursday, the
president also called for more regional and international
cooperation in combating terrorism.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the need for international dialogue and
understanding to educate and soften the hearts of those afflicted
by fundamentalist ideologies.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania were attacked almost
simultaneously on August 7, 1998, leaving more than 200 people
dead and 5,000 people injured. 
</P>
