<HEADLINE> Angolan Customs Earns Over $120 Million in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan Customs earned over 120
million U.S. dollars in 1999, said Director of the country's
Customhouse Mateus da Rosa on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by official newspaper Jornal de Angola as saying
that 80 percent of this amount came from customs posts in the
capital city of Luanda, particularly the "February 4th"
International Airport, whose monthly earning is estimated at some
one million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Although the head of the Customhouse did not mention the figure
in the previous year, local analysts said the Customs had seen a
hike in the earning.
</P>
<P>
According to Rosa, the increment of the earning is mainly due
to the program "Tolerance Zero" which was masterminded by the
customhouse in the past year with an aim to curb fraud and tax
evasion and to reinforce control over the administration of the
customhouse. 
</P>
