<HEADLINE> Nigeria Demands Explanation of Citizen Maltreatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria Thursday demanded "urgent
information" on alleged recent maltreatment of its citizens by the
French and Cote d' Ivoire governments in their countries, reported
The Guardian, a leading Nigerian newspaper, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Nigerian Foreign Minister Alhaji
Lamido commended Akinwumi Isola, who brought the French incident
into focus last month through a report in a Nigerian newspaper.
</P>
<P>
