known in his report the arrest and trial of 10 people for
protesting the dehumanizing manner a Nigerian was being deported
at Charles de Gaulle International Airport in France on January
20.
</P>
<P>
In another development, a Nigerian paraplegic patient was
arrested at Houphouet Boigny Airport in Abidjan, Cote d'Ivoire on
February 21 and is currently in prison for inexplicable reasons.
</P>
<P>
The French embassy in Lagos, reports said, had earlier given
assurance that the case would be amicably resolved, as the home
country desires good bilateral relations with Nigeria. 
