<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Effective Measures Urged For Preventing Accidental Injuries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese medical expert said
that preventive measures of sanitary science can reduce the
occurrence of accidental injuries.
</P>
<P>
He Zhesheng, a researcher from the Zhejiang Provincial Academy
of Medical Science, said prevention and control of accidental
injuries is a systematic project involving departments and units
in the fields of sanitation, public security, industries,
consumption, culture and education, science and technology, sports,
social security, tourism, and trade unions and women organizations.
</P>
<P>
Research has found that all the aforementioned sectors have a
close relation with the occurrence of accidental injuries. He said
that the government should work out strategies, regulations and
measures for controlling accidental injuries, and make the public
aware to prevent such injuries from occurring.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that accidental injuries caused some 600,000
deaths annually and because of such injuries, 20 million people
are hospitalized or have emergency treatment annually.
</P>
<P>
Accidental injuries have become the fourth leading killer
following respiratory tract diseases, malign tumors and
cerebrovascular diseases in China.
</P>
<P>
Since the late 1980s China has established an accidental
injuries network. Injuries monitoring cover traffic accident,
accidental poisoning, falling, medical malpractice, fire, drowning,
suicide and homicide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0186 </DOCNO>
