<HEADLINE> Heavy Snow Closes Airport in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The airport in Changchun,
capital of northeast China's Jilin Province, was closed this
morning because of a heavy snow that hit the city yesterday
evening.
</P>
<P>
Strong winds and rain appeared on Thursday afternoon, followed
later by snow in the evening, said Zhu Qiwen, head of the
provincial meteorological observatory.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said it is rare to see such a heavy snow in the city in
early April, and the snowfall is continuing.
</P>
<P>
Airport officials said flights from the airport to Beijing,
Shanghai, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, and other cities were postponed, as
the staff remains busy cleaning the snow from the runways.
</P>
<P>
Sources also said that all railways and expressways in the
province are open, and no serious traffic accidents have been
reported so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
