<HEADLINE> MOFTEC Official on Foreign Trade, Economic Cooperation in China's West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) Zhang Xiang has urged China's vast
western region to take advantage of special characteristics in
developing trade and economic cooperation with overseas countries.
</P>
<P>
The west should first of all take advantage of its special
industries and map out strategies encouraging exports, first
targeting increased added value for its export products, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the west should map out medium- and long-term
policies to attract foreign investment, especially in the reform
of state-owned enterprises. The west also should endeavor to
create a better investment environment and try to make all state-
level economic and technological development zones a success.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted in particular that the west should take full
advantage of its ecological resources and strengthen the
construction of its ecological environment. Exports of
agricultural products and tourism can become two ways to promote
foreign trade and economic cooperation, he said. 
</P>
