<HEADLINE> Australia Leads Germany 2-0 in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Davis Cup holder Australia took a
comfortable lead over Germany by winning both singles matches in
its quarter-final clash against Germany in Adelaide on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Teenager Lleyton Hewitt outclassed a nervous Michael Kohlmann 6-
1, 6-1, 6-2 in the opening singles before Wayne Arthurs overcame
David Prinosil 7-6, 3-6, 7-6, 6-7, 11-9 for a 2-0 lead for the
defending champion.
</P>
<P>
By winning one of the three remaining matches, Australia will
secure a home semifinal against either Brazil or Slovakia in July.
</P>
<P>
Hewitt, ranked 11th in the world, defeated his older opponent
in the opening match which lasted just 80 minutes as Kohlmann only
came to Australia as a hitting partner for his teammates and was
only ushered onto the grass court after Rainer Schuettler withdrew
with an injury on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, Arthurs was pushed all the way by Prinosil, who is
ranked nine places ahead of him at 93rd in the world.
</P>
<P>
Arthurs, a replacement for injured Mark Philippoussis, won the
first and third sets in tiebreakers then held match point in the
fourth, but Prinosil survived and went on to win the tiebreaker to
force for a deciding fifth set.
</P>
<P>
The German saved two match points in the 14th and 16th games
before Arthurs broke him in the 20th game to seal victory after
four and a quarter hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
