<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chengjiang Fossils to Apply for World Heritage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China plans to apply for UNESCO's
World Natural Heritage listing for the arthropod fossil stratum
site located in Chengjiang county in southwest China's Yunnan
Province.
</P>
<P>
Chengjiang fossils, dating back some 500 million years,include
large quantities of tiny multicellular animals and their embryos,
which are said to be the earliest multicellular animals on Earth.
Their discovery has led to significant breakthroughs in attempts
to understand human evolution.
</P>
<P>
The first discovery was made in July 1984 by Hou Xianguang, a
research fellow with the Nanjing Institute of Geology and
Paleontology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences when he conducted
field investigations at Maotian Mountain in Chengjiang County, the
original discovery site.
</P>
<P>
To date, Hou has discovered more than 10,000 fossils in 17
speciations. The most important ones include Yunnan Zoon,
microdictyon, anomalocaris and fuxianhuia.
</P>
<P>
With the aid of Jan Bergstrom, an scholar from the Sweden Royal
Academy, Hou made a systematic and comprehensive research on
fossils found in Chengjiang and published 40-odd academic papers
on the subject.
</P>
<P>
"Chengjiang fossils are miracles in the evolution of organisms
in the formation of Earth. These fossils offer valuable research
on human evolution dating back to 530 million years ago," Hou said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ITU Adopts Chinese IP Standard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 7 (Xinhua)-- A proposal regarding IP technology
put forward by a group of scientists at the Wuhan Posts and
Telecommunications Academy has been accepted by International
Telecommunications Union (ITU) as an international standard.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Yu Shaohua, who was responsible for the program, explained
that their IP standard, dubbed "IP over SDH (Synchronous Digital
Hierarchy)," successfully solved the problem of operating IP on
SDH optical cable so that telecommunications network and computer
networks can be combined, and with this new standard Internet
surfing will be much faster than now.
</P>
<P>
According to Yu, the Chinese IP standard was first put forward
to ITU in July 1998, and was formally adopted as an international
standard for IP technology by ITU on March 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
The present commonly used IP standard is one developed by
American scientists. The adoption of the Chinese IP standard as
an international standard by ITU is of far-reaching significance
for the development of China's IT, said Dr. Yu Shaohua. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aquiculture Reports Big Growth In Coastal City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo, a coastal city in east
China's Zhejiang Province, registered 2.144 billion yuan in output
value in aquiculture last year, a nearly five percent rise on a
yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The increase is a result of the introduction of preferential
policies to encourage individuals and units to invest in breeding
aquatic products locally.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city invested more than 200 million yuan in
seawater aquiculture and added nearly 8,666 ha. of breeding areas,
bringing the total to 39,800 ha.
</P>
<P>
The city also introduced good strains of aquatic products,
fodder and new technology. The city has established more than 30
baby aquatic lives breeding center, which can provide more than
two billion young shrimps, 10 million fries and 500 million baby
crabs per year.
</P>
<P>
The average income for per capita of local fishermen reached 7,
434 yuan last year, a 6.32 percent rise from 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
