<HEADLINE> Russia Publishes Final Results of Presidential Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Russian governmental newspaper
Rossiiskaya Gazeta on Friday published the final official results
of the country's March 26 presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Russian Acting President Vladimir Putin collected 39,740,434
votes or 52.94 percent of the total votes cast, Communist Party
leader Gennady Zyuganov got 21,928,471 and Yabloko movement leader
Grigory Yavlinsky was in the third place with 4,351,452.
</P>
<P>
The other candidates did not clear the 3-percent barrier,
according to the Central Election Commission
</P>
<P>
Under existing Russian legislation, the inauguration of
President elect Vladimir Putin will be held on May 7, the 30th day
after the official publication of the election results by the
Central Election Commission.
</P>
<P>
The commission declared the election valid at its Wednesday
session and approved the returns. 
</P>
