<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing High-tech Industries Week Attracts More Int'l Organizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 43 international
organizations and foreign government and enterprise delegations
have signed in for the Third Beijing International High-Tech
Industries Week scheduled for May 8-12.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee for the event said today that many
international organizations have become co-sponsors of activities
at the week-long event.
</P>
<P>
These activities include a symposium on foreign bank
involvement in China's key projects, and a seminar on cooperation
between the European Union and small and medium-sized enterprises
in China.
</P>
<P>
The representative office of the United Nations Development
Program in China will be one of the organizers of an international
symposium on technological cooperation among developing countries.
</P>
