<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Auction Off Part of Its Cotton Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China plans to auctioned off part
of its cotton reserves this month to improve cotton supply and
demand and stop price hikes.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the All China Federation of Supply and Marketing
Cooperatives (ACFSMC) said all legal textile and cotton
enterprises will be eligible to take part in the public bidding.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of cotton reserves will be sold on April 10,
said an ACFSMC source.
</P>
<P>
Prices of first-grade cotton went up from 8,800 per ton earlier
this year to the present 12,000 yuan per ton. Experts attributed
the price hike to decreased cotton production in 1999 and an
increasing consumption demand at present.
</P>
<P>
"However, the price surge doesn't mean China's cotton resources
is in shortage. It merely indicates that there is a gap between
last year's cotton output and this year's consumption demand, "
said an official with ACFSMC.
</P>
<P>
The cotton consumption for 2000 is estimated at 76 million dan
(one dan equals to 50 kilograms). There might be a temporary gap
between demand and supply, the official noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0254 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sinopec Plans Larger Retail Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China National Petrochemical Corp.
(Sinopec), the country's leading petrochemical products
manufacturer, plans to invest 31.3 billion yuan (about 38 billion
U.S. dollars) to expand its retail business during the 2000-2003
period.
</P>
<P>
Of this total investment, 25.1 billion will be used to purchase
gas stations and build new stations in major cities and along
highways, according to the China Information News.
</P>
<P>
The other 6.2 billion yuan will go to facilities for the
storage and transportation of petroleum.
</P>
<P>
Sinopec expects its retail market share to rise from 40 percent
in 1999 to 70 percent in 2003 after this new investment.
</P>
</TEXT>
