<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0255 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Entrepreneurs Confidence Surges to New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese entrepreneur confidence in
the economy surged to a new high over the past eight quarters in
the first three months of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to figures that the National Bureau of Statistics (
NBS) released today, the index of entrepreneur confidence rose by
10.6 percentage points over the previous quarter to 11.3 percent
in the first quarter of the year, an increase of 14.8 percentage
points over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
NBS said in a report that the surge of entrepreneur confidence
was due to sound economic situation, implementation of the
national strategy of developing the western part of China and the
prospect of China's accession to the World Trade Organization (WTO)
.
</P>
<P>
Chinese enterprises enjoyed stable performance in the first
quarter. The index of performance dipped 0.2 percentage points
over the previous quarter but rose by 3.5 percentage points over
the first quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
The index of confidence for heads of state-owned enterprises
showed a turn about from negative to positive zones in the first
quarter of the year. Confidence of entrepreneurs in the industries
of pipeline transport and oil and natural gas exploration improved
greatly.
</P>
<P>
The prospective WTO accession of China also helped boost the
confidence of textile and garment entrepreneurs to an all-time
high in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
During January to March, specific indicators of production,
sales and inventories have all improved over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the index of performance of such industries
as transport and communication, storage, post and
telecommunications, real estate, retail and wholesale trade and
catering services were improving. But the index of performance of
housing and social service industries fell over the same period of
last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
