<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Cultural News: Weekly Highlights (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Top Think Tank Organizes Regular Symposia on Policies
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Academy of Social Sciences (CASS), China's top
think tank, has decided to establish a fortnightly symposia system
to discuss the country's important policies.
</P>
<P>
The CASS has organized lots of leading experts and well-known
scholars to make suggestions on such issues as China's entry into
the World Trade Organization, the ambitious plan on westward
development, reforms on state-owned enterprises, grain price and
educational structure.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Pay Tribute to Legendary Ancestor
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of people from all walks of life participated
in activities on April 4 in the city of Baoji to commemorate Yan
Di, one of two legendary ancestors of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Baoji, in northwest China's Shaanxi Province, is believed to be
the native home of Yan Di, also known as Shennong, and April 5 is
the Chinese Qingming Festival, an occasion for people to visit
ancestral graves.
</P>
<P>
Chinese History Encyclopedia Published
</P>
<P>
After 22 years, nearly 1,000 Chinese historians have finally
completed "The Chinese History Encyclopedia" .
</P>
<P>
It has recently been published by the Shanghai Lexicographic
Publishing House. The 11 million-word dictionary, the nation's
most authoritative historical dictionary, includes nearly 70,000
entries, covering historical events from the early Qin Dynasty (
221 B.C. - 207 B.C.) to the end of the Qing Dynasty (1644 - 1911).
</P>
<P>
Chinese Artists to Help Develop Western Region
</P>
<P>
The China Federation of Literary and Art Circles announced on
April 6 that it has launched a series of projects to assist the
underdeveloped western region of the country to mark the fifth
anniversary of President Jiang Zemin's letter to local artists.
</P>
<P>
These projects have been designed to respond to the central
leadership's strategy of developing the economically backward
western region on a large scale, according to officials from the
federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
