<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mynamar Govt Urges Opposition to Act Constructively </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar military government
Thursday urged the opposition National League for Democracy (NLD)
to act in a more responsible and constructive manner without
adding hardship to the country while it is working to develop
Myanmar and rejoin the world community.
</P>
<P>
The government charged in a statement available here Friday
that the NLD as well as some foreign governments are in favor of
using the method of confrontation in dealing with the State Peace
and Development Council (SPDC), the military's ruling body, saying
that the SPDC is merely a caretaker or transitional government.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the SPDC has discarded the one-party
socialist system for a multi-party democratic system and has also
introduced a market economy, enabling Myanmar, a war-torn country
not too long ago, to become one of the most peaceful and stable
countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
The government has, in fact, kept and is still keeping the
doors open for those who desire to cooperate with it for the
development of Myanmar, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement urged the NLD to avoid all actions that are
detrimental to the interests of the nation and its people. It also
encouraged the opposition party to try to achieve its political
goal and the nation's goal of transforming Myanmar into a stable
and multi-party democracy with a thriving economy through shared
responsibility and cooperation but not confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The statement went on to say that the Myanmar government,
together with many other developing and developed countries, share
the concept that for the third world countries, the most important
rights for the mass population are the basic human needs, without
fulfillment of which, it added, it is absolutely not possible to
achieve sustainable development and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The statement warned that the development of the people of
those developing countries should not be hampered in anyway by
having the U.N Charter being manipulated and exploited as a tool
and leverage.
</P>
<P>
The statement welcome constructive advice as well as criticism
without ill-intention.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the NLD blamed in a recent statement that the
government is still refusing to implement the result of the 1990
multi-party general election, in which the NLD won 396
parliamentary seats out of 485.
</P>
<P>
On the contrary, the statement said, the government applies
various means to stop and disturb all efforts aimed at demanding
the emergence of the people's parliament. As a result, the country
continues to be in the crisis in the fields of politics, economy,
education, social and international affairs, it added.
</P>
<P>
The NLD's statement warned that the only way out to tackle
Myanmar's present overall crisis is to follow the people's desire
and transfer back the state power to the people's representatives.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
