<HEADLINE> U.S. Lucent to Expand Production in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Lucent Technologies of Shanghai
Ltd., a Sino-U.S. joint venture, will begin to establish five new
production lines in May, bringing its total number of production
lines to six.
</P>
<P>
The expansion also including 32,000 square-meter workshops,
scheduled to be operational in July 2001, will cost 45 million U.S.
dollars, half of which will come from the U.S. Lucent Technologies
Optical Networking Group.
</P>
<P>
Dai Aoqian, chairman of Shanghai Lucent, said that his company
is expected to become one of the U.S. Lucent' three key production
centers in the world after the expansion is put into operation.
</P>
<P>
According to Dai, their recent decision to enlarge production
in China has been prompted by Shanghai Lucent's good performance.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture, co-funded by three Chinese enterprises,
including the Shanghai Posts and Telecommunications Equipment
Company, and the U.S. Lucent Technologies Optical Networking Group,
has made profits for the past 11 years running.
</P>
<P>
Holding a 35 percent share of the Chinese market, Shanghai
Lucent has already become the biggest optical transmission
equipment supplier in this country.
</P>
<P>
The company is expected to generate 240 million U.S. dollars in
output value this year, up 60 percent from last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
