<HEADLINE> Report Shows China in Next 50 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A report looking at China in the
next 50 years, the result of a symposium on China held last
November in the United Kingdom, has been distributed in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Former President of Australia Bob Hawke, who attended a
ceremony where the report was issued, said the document "China
Beyond Fifty" by Richard L Grant, is "a crystallization of the
ideas and opinions of some of the most respected minds on China
today," Friday's China Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
Organized by Wilton Park Conferences and XRG-Exceptional
Resources Group, the symposium attracted 50 senior officials,
scholars and business people around the globe.
</P>
