<HEADLINE> Private Businesses Advertise for Youth League Cadres </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Ten private businesses in Shaoxing
City of east China's province Zhejiang have jointly advertised
nationwide for secretary candidates of the Communist Youth League.
</P>
<P>
Once admitted, these Communist Youth League cadres with these
companies will be offered a yearly salary that is not below 30,000
yuan (about 3,600 U.S. dollars), according to today's China Youth
Daily.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that private businesses in the province
joined hands in soliciting with high salaries for competent youth
leaders, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
According to the advertisement, the candidates should be member
of the Chinese Communist Party or the Communist Youth League below
the age of 30.
</P>
<P>
They should have above-college level education, good personal
quality and knowledge of enterprise management.
</P>
<P>
Private businesses in Shaoxing have been developing very
rapidly in recent years. So far, private businesses account for
about two thirds of the total gross domestic product (GDP) of the
city.
</P>
<P>
The businesses that participated in the advertising are all
promising private enterprises, including the Zhongyi Group, the
province's largest private business, with an annual sale of one
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The private sector in the province has been booming for more
than a decade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
