<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0310 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ROK Becomes Shandong's Leading Trade Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Republic of Korea (ROK) has
become the leading trade partner of east China's Shandong Province,
and bilateral trade volume is growing rapidly.
</P>
<P>
Statistics provided by the Qingdao customs show that the trade
volume between the two sides reached 689 million US dollars in the
first two months of this year, up 48 percent over last year's
corresponding period.
</P>
<P>
The figure exceeded the trade volume between Shandong and Japan
in the January-February period.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, Shandong's exports to the ROK were
valued at 261 million dollars, and imports were worth 428 million
dollars, increases of 50.9 percent and 46.8 percent, respectively,
over last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's exporters are mainly processing and foreign-funded
enterprises, and their export commodities include electro-
mechanical products, garments, shoes, pig iron, textiles and
aquatic products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
