<HEADLINE> Developed Guangdong Eyes Western Region Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south China,
one of China's most developed regions, signed Thursday nearly 100
cooperative projects valued at 13 billion yuan, at an investment
and trade fair.
</P>
<P>
The Investment and Trade Fair for Cooperation Between East and
West China is being held in this capital of Shaanxi Province, in
the northwest of the country.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong now ranked the first among China's 20 provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities in terms of the signed
contract value, on the first day of the fair.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong Governor Lu Ruihua said that the state policy to spur
the economic development of the vast western area has not only
brought "historical opportunities" for that region, but also new
development opportunities for developed eastern area.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong will certainly grasp this development opportunity,
said Lu, who headed 500 enterprises and over 1,000 businessmen to
participate in the fair, which is scheduled to close April 9.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that Guangdong will sign contracts for some 360
cooperative projects with enterprises from the western area during
the trade fair. The projects will cover high-tech,
telecommunications and infrastructure facility sectors.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's economy accounts for over one tenth of the country'
s total, and its foreign trade volume for one third of the total.
Its economy has grown at a phenomenal rate since China adopted the
reform and opening policies in the late 1970s. 
</P>
