<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: World Health Day 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The seventh day of each April is
designated as World Health Day, which will focus on global issues
of blood safety this year.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-two years ago, the date witnessed official establishment
of the World Health Organization (WHO), and its annual assembly in
1950 designated the day as World Health Day.
</P>
<P>
The objective of World Health Day is to raise global awareness
of a specific health theme to highlight a priority area of concern
for the WHO. The day serves as a launch for a long-term advocacy
program for which activities will be undertaken and resources
provided well beyond 7 April.
</P>
<P>
"World Health Day 2000" has been dedicated to the theme of
Blood Safety and to the slogan "Safe blood starts with me".
</P>
<P>
The objectives of World Health Day 2000 are:
</P>
<P>
To raise awareness of blood safety issues globally.
</P>
<P>
To encourage Member States, including China, to commit to and
support national blood programs and implement national blood
legislation or a legal framework for a national blood program to
ensure the provision of safe blood.
</P>
<P>
To promote and retain donations from voluntary (altruistic),
non-remunerated blood donors from low-risk populations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0318 </DOCNO>
