<HEADLINE> Bergkamp Gives Arsenal Edge in UEFA Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 6 (Xinhua) -- English premier league soccer club
Arsenal took a step closer to the UEFA Cup final, as Dennis
Bergkamp's early goal gave them a slender lead after the first leg
of their semi-final at Highbury against Racing Lens.
</P>
<P>
Bergkamp put the Gunners ahead after just two minutes - but the
rest of the game proved a frustrating affair for Arsene Wenger's
side and unfancied Lens did enough to keep the tie in the balance.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal were expected to find life relatively easy against the
team rated as the weakest of the four semi-finalists.
</P>
<P>
And when Bergkamp found the net right at the start of the game
and Nwankwo Kanu was presented with two gilt-edged chances soon
after, it looked like being a stroll for the north Londoners.
</P>
<P>
But Lens proved they are more than mere makeweights in this
year's competition and will fancy their chances of causing an
upset in the return leg in two weeks. 
</P>
