<DOCNO> XIE20000407.0324 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nude Photo Exhibition Cold Shouldered in Harbin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of photographs
featuring nudity did not intrigue many people in this city with a
population of nearly 10 million.
</P>
<P>
Only about 200 people have visited the exhibition during the
past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Harbin is the capital city of northeast China's Heilongjiang
Province, neighboring Russia.
</P>
<P>
Over 120 pictures are on display. They were all taken in Russia
using local models by photographers from the province last year.
</P>
<P>
"We were worried at first that the exhibition might arouse a
great disturbance," said Li Qian, secretary-general of the
provincial society of artistic photography. "It seems now that our
worries were groundless."
</P>
<P>
In the visitors' book for the exhibition, some visitors wrote
"Creation and nature make perfection", "The courage to display the
beauty of the human body is social progress", and "We enjoyed the
exhibition, as bodily beauty is a kind of natural beauty too".
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will last for one month here, and then will go
on tour across the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
