<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Banks Urged to Help Small Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 6 (Xinhua) -- South African Trade and
Industry Minister Alec Erwin on Thursday urged banks to do more to
help small businesses so as to create more jobs, South African
Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's banks have performed poorly in helping small
businesses, Erwin said during a debate on the trade and industry
budget in the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
He said the banks' lack of familiarity with the black community
had made them react slowly to job creation through small and micro
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
His ministry intended to intervene more decisively in the
creation of small businesses, he said.
</P>
<P>
Erwin said the promotion of small business and black economic
empowerment would remain at the top of the department's agenda
over the next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
