<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2110GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN -- An Italian pilot detained by Jordan on
charges of violating its airspace could be
released without trial and get back his small,
confiscated aircraft, the semi-official Jordan
Times reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The pilot, identified as Claudio Castagna, was
detained for questioning Wednesday after his plane
was intercepted by two Jordanian fighter planes
and forced to land down at Azraq airport, 80
kilometers east of Amman.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian Minister of Information Saleh Qallab
said whether to allow him to leave the kingdom
depends on the prosecutor's decision.(Jordan-
Italian Pilot)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus has overcome a political
hurdle in its European Union accession
negotiations as it concluded the talks on common
and foreign security policy (CFSP) with the EU,
local media reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed in Brussels on Thursday to
close the CFSP chapter and three less problematic
chapters: social and employment policy, fisheries
and company law, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The closure of the four chapters means Cyprus
has provisionally closed 15 of a total of 30
chapters. It also assuages the doubts that the
division of Cyprus could impede the island's
accession course. (Cyprus-EU Accession)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- The United Nations Interim Force in
Lebanon (UNIFIL) said Friday that it has no
mandate to disarm the Palestinians in refugee
camps in the country, An-Nahar newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
UNIFIL spokesman Timor Goksel said the
Palestinian refugee camps were outside UNIFIL's
area of operation in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese President Emile Lahoud said in a
memorandum after talking here with U.N. Secretary-
General Kofi Annan's envoy Roid Larsen that the U.
N. peacekeepers should disarm Palestinian refugees
in Lebanon after Israel's withdrawal from south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Lahoud expressed concern that Palestinian
guerrillas would continue attacks after Israel's
unilateral withdrawal from south Lebanon. Lebanese
government can not entirely control Palestinian
guerrillas so they will not be responsible for the
possible attacks, he hinted. (Lebanon-UN)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
