<HEADLINE> Third Rally in Tech Stocks Lifts Nasdaq Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The technology stocks rallied in
the third consecutive session Friday after Tuesday's rocky swings,
lifting the Nasdaq index higher.
</P>
<P>
At the close of session, the technology heavy Nasdaq composite
index rose 178.89 or 4.1 percent at 4,446.45. The index rose 98.34
points Thursday and 20.33 points Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. The Dow Jones
industrial average fell slightly 2.79 at 11,111.48 and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 15.01 at 1,516.35.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq index rose as investors continued to show their
enthusiasm for the technology stocks in the third straight session.
Qualcomm and JDS Uniphase led the Nasdaq's advance.
</P>
<P>
The recent wild rides in the technology stocks dragged the
Nasdaq composite down 349.15 points Monday and 574.57 points
before marching back Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Investors were encouraged by an employment report today. The
Labor Department said the U.S. unemployment rate held steady at 4.
1 percent in March, above the 4 percent in expectations and the
average hourly earnings rose 0.4 percent in the same period, also
in line with estimates.
</P>
<P>
Another report on job increases did not affect the tech market.
The report said a strong 416,000 jobs were added to business
payrolls in March, the largest gain since February, 1999, which
could attempt the Federal Reserve to raise interest rates again.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve has raised the rates five times since last
June in an effort to ward off the build-up of inflation.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 10.49 at 542.
99.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,537 up, 1,427 down and 491
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 888.39 million shares from 999.37
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
