</P>
<P>
Denying China PNTR status does not present China from joining
the WTO; it only presents the United States from having greater
access to China's markets, said the largest air carrier in the
world.
</P>
<P>
United Airlines is seeking to operate more air service to China.
The airline currently offers nonstop flights between San Francisco
and Shanghai five days each week, and is urging the U.S.
Department of Transportation to grant it the two remaining
frequencies it needs to provide daily nonstop service. In June,
United will launch daily nonstop service between San Francisco and
Beijing, and the airline will launch another Shanghai daily
nonstop service next year from Chicago, the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
